FACTION: THE PALE COURT
Leader: Valerius Caelinus (genuine ~32nd-in-line Caelus claimant, publicly overstating
  himself as 4th-5th; see Npcs/Valerius Sec. II)
Base of Operations: Solitude (Proudspire Manor; working toward the Blue Palace)
Archetype: Political/Supernatural Tyranny — domination through dependency, not force
Core Philosophy: "The Empire is dying. The Stormcloaks are children playing with sticks.
  Only an Eternal King can offer true stability."

=====================================================================
I. THE ASCENSION CLOCK
=====================================================================
Tier 0: Infiltration — COMPLETE. Valerius arrived in Solitude, bought Proudspire Manor
  with ancient gold, presented himself as a wealthy Cyrodiilic noble with an ancient (and
  genuine, if overstated) genealogy, and began buying access to Jarl Elisif through war
  donations.

Tier 1: The Shadow Cabinet — CURRENT.
  Action: Removing Elisif's trusted advisors. Falk Firebeard discredited or "falls ill."
  Sybille Stentor (a fellow vampire) coerced into alliance or marginalized.
  World State: Solitude guards more aggressive; curfews enforced; beggars and dissidents
  quietly disappear.
  Orion's (former) role: sabotage rivals in the court. Now MOOT — Orion disobeyed at the
  Grelod kill and is being reasserted as a leash, not a working agent (see Npcs/Valerius
  Sec. VI, the Orion failure ladder). The off-hand reckoning IS this tier's next beat.

Tier 2: The Bloodline Claim — trigger UPDATED. The original trigger ("discovery of the
  Jagged Crown") is now a DEAD LEAD — the Crown is permanently corrupted into the Crown
  of Namira, carried by Alfonso, and can never be recovered or worn as a legitimacy
  symbol. Valerius does not know this yet; when he learns Alfonso is the one who ruined
  it, that discovery becomes the trigger for his death-and-ruin campaign against Alfonso
  (Npcs/Valerius Sec. VI.2), NOT for this tier.
  This tier now runs on the OVERSTATED GENEALOGY ALONE: he publicly reveals his
  "heritage," claims descent from a lost First-Era High King predating the Septims, and
  argues the Mede dynasty is illegitimate and Ulfric a usurper.
  The Proposal: he formally courts Jarl Elisif. A marriage would unite her current claim
  with his ancient (overstated) bloodline.
  World State: Solitude nobility, desperate for a strong leader, begins to back him.

Tier 3: The Dark Coronation.
  Trigger: the wedding is announced.
  Action: the Moot is bribed, threatened, or enthralled. He raises the Volkihar Guard —
  vampire elites in plate who serve as his Royal Guard and walk openly at night.
  The offer: a place as his High Generals, in exchange for helping him purge the Dragon
  Cult (his only rival for dominion).

Tier 4: The Eternal Kingdom (endgame).
  Skyrim becomes a cattle farm — "protected," fed upon, law absolute, freedom zero.
  Mechanical hook: the Dawnguard-lore "Sun Tyranny" arrow, used to permanently dim the
  sun so his court can rule by day.

